to the editor re quietly the first lady builds a literary room of her own white house letter front page oct 7 it is certainly commendable that laura bush is so dedicated to american literature that she is willing to move beyond ideological divisions otherwise separating her from many scholars but her statement that there 's nothing political about american literature is misleading if not naive consider langston hughes a poet she admires i swear to the lord i still ca n't see why democracy means everybody but me in fact most of hughes 's poetry likewise focuses on the oppression and disenfranchisement of african americans in what was the jim crow nation surely the works of other writers mentioned twain faulkner cather were inspired in some shape or form by the authors political interests perhaps even by their partisanship hampton carey redding conn oct 7 2002

